title.narrative: Harm Reduction for Key Populations

description.narrative: Mauritius - HIV - Ministry of Health and Wellness - MOH & W. This program has the following goals: Diagnose 95% of all PLHIV by 2030. Start 95% of those diagnosed with HIV on ART by 2030. Achieve viral suppression for 95% of patients on ART by 2030. The objectives of this program are: Improve prevention programs for key and vulnerable populations. Improve testing services through a more effective and efficient differentiated testing services. Improve treatment adherence and retention in care by more efficient use of peer-educators and adherence counsellors
